<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 6:30PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of
east central Craig, southwestern Rockbridge, northern Bedford,
Botetourt and west central Amherst Counties through 700 PM EDT...
At 630 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Snowden to near New Castle. Movement was
east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Amherst...
Buchanan...
Glasgow...
Troutville...
New Castle...
Big Island...
and Fincastle.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
southeastern West Virginia.</instruction>
